stylometry: Decisions trees are important becasue they are used in decision analysis to help identify a strategy most likely to reach a goal. An example of how a decision tree can be used to solve a problem was the one about a realitor having the choice of investing in either a warehouse, office buidling, or apartment.  In this certain model we used a decision tree to find out the chances and percentages as to what was the best way to go.
